.TH "key_update" 9 "key_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
key_update \- Update a key's contents.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" key_update
.BI "(key_ref_t key_ref "  ","
.BI "const void *payload "  ","
.BI "size_t plen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "key_ref" 12
The pointer (plus possession flag) to the key.
.IP "payload" 12
The data to be used to update the key.
.IP "plen" 12
The length of \fIpayload\fP.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Attempt to update the contents of a key with the given payload data.  The
caller must be granted Write permission on the key.  Negative keys can be
instantiated by this method.

Returns 0 on success, -EACCES if not permitted and -EOPNOTSUPP if the key
type does not support updating.  The key type may return other errors.
